"""
Ark-compatible DEQ gradient-flow ODE — DEQAnalogCkt.
dz/dt = tanh(W_z @ z + W_x @ x_input + b_x) - z
State augmented: y = [z, x_input]  (dim=128),  dx_input/dt = 0.

At equilibrium (dz/dt = 0): z* = f_theta(z*, x_input).
rho(df_theta/dz) < 1 guarantees convergence (spectral norm enforced).

Architecture: z_dim=64, x_dim=64, tanh activation.
Total trainable params: 8256  (W_z:4096, W_x:4096, b_x:64)
Mismatch sigma=0.05 on all weight matrices.

Usage:
    from ark.optimization.base_module import TimeInfo
    import jax.numpy as jnp
    ckt = DEQAnalogCkt()
    # y0 = [z0, x_input] — z0=zeros, x_input=your analog input
    y0 = jnp.zeros(128)
    time_info = TimeInfo(t0=0.0, t1=5.0, dt0=0.1, saveat=jnp.array([5.0]))
    z_star = ckt(time_info, y0, switch=jnp.array([]), args_seed=42, noise_seed=43)
"""

